      "snippet": "Address not found Your message wasn&#39;t delivered to feedback@medtechsolutions.com because the address couldn&#39;t be found, or is unable to receive mail. LEARN MORE This link will take you to a",
      "body": "Dear MedTech Solutions Team,\r\n\r\nThank you for inviting us to provide feedback on the patient profile\r\nmanagement system you have deployed at Harmony Health Clinic. We have\r\nbeen using the platform for roughly a year and would like to share\r\nboth the strengths we have experienced and a few opportunities for\r\nfurther enhancement.\r\n\r\n1. Ease of Use & Workflow Efficiency\r\n•  The interface is intuitive, which has shortened staff onboarding time.\r\n•  Pre-built templates (e.g., the “Personal Profile” format we use for\r\npatients such as Alex Thompson) make it easy to record communication\r\npreferences, sensory sensitivities and daily routines in one place.\r\n•  Clinicians can locate critical information at the point of care,\r\nreducing hand-off errors and helping us achieve a smoother daily\r\nworkflow.\r\n\r\n2. Data Handling & Privacy\r\n•  Encryption in transit and at rest, plus the audit log, give us\r\nconfidence that PHI is protected.\r\n•  We would appreciate the option for field-level, role-based access\r\ncontrols so that, for example, medication details can be limited to\r\nprescribing providers while still allowing support staff to see\r\nnon-clinical preferences.\r\n•  Automated consent-management workflows (e.g., alerts when a\r\npatient’s data-sharing consent nears expiration) would help us stay\r\ncompliant without manual monitoring.\r\n\r\n3. Interoperability\r\n•  The FHIR-compliant export works well; however inbound integration\r\nwith our legacy EHR still requires manual mapping of custom fields.\r\nProviding a sandbox with sample payloads would accelerate our\r\nintegration work.\r\n•  A real-time API for bi-directional updates would prevent data\r\ndivergence between systems.\r\n\r\n4. Analytics & Outcomes Tracking\r\n•  Since implementation we have seen an 18 % increase in the\r\ncompleteness of follow-up data, which in turn correlates with improved\r\npatient outcome tracking (see our “Patient Profile Management –\r\nGeneral Statistics” report).\r\n•  Having built-in dashboards—especially for adherence to care plans\r\nand medication schedules—would let clinicians act on insights without\r\nexporting data to a separate BI tool.\r\n\r\n5. Feature Requests & Future Enhancements\r\n•  Customizable alert rules that can, for instance, flag when a\r\nmedication refill is overdue or when a patient’s sensory profile\r\nconflicts with a scheduled procedure.\r\n•  Expanded multi-factor authentication options (hardware token or\r\nauthenticator app) to complement SMS.\r\n•  Offline mode with automatic sync for community or home visits where\r\nconnectivity is unreliable.\r\n•  Ability to anonymize or de-identify patient data on export to\r\nfacilitate research collaborations.\r\n\r\nOverall, the system has streamlined how we collect, store and act on\r\npatient information, and it has had a measurable positive impact on\r\ncontinuity of care. We appreciate your collaborative approach and\r\nwould be happy to walk through our workflow or provide additional\r\ndetails if useful.\r\n\r\nThank you again for your commitment to advancing patient-centred technology.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\n[Your Name]\r\nVendor Partner, Harmony Health Clinic\r\n[Your Contact Information]\r\n"
    }
